So with the IT--you IT folks,
you know that you test out a deployment

00:06:02.390 --> 00:06:07.380
before you roll it out to your customers,
or disaster will happen in most cases.

00:06:07.450 --> 00:06:11.070
So what happens is,
as you're deploying that,

00:06:11.250 --> 00:06:15.360
you find the glitches and the gutches,
and you've been giving us feedback

00:06:15.360 --> 00:06:17.400
on some of those implementations,
and we've taken those to heart.

00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:19.400
So we'll be discussing some of those.

00:06:19.400 --> 00:06:24.400
And where we're going to be taking
Apple desktop management going forward.

00:06:24.400 --> 00:06:28.360
I'll be showing you a little
bit about what's new in 10.3,

00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:30.110
